alse, "description": "Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints"}, {"id": 211668100, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTE2NjgxMDA=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-compiler", "name": "T-compiler", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 900795185, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw5MDA3OTUxODU=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-const-eval", "name": "A-const-eval", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: constant evaluation (mir interpretation)"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2019-10-19T13:50:59Z", "updated_at": "2020-06-11T17:32:08Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Consider:\r\n```rust\r\n#![allow(const_err)]\r\n\r\nunion Trans { i: usize, o: &'static u32 }\r\n\r\nconst C: () = unsafe { let _val = *Trans { i: 4 }.o; () };\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", C);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThis deref's a dangling pointer, but due to `allow(const_err)` the only diagnostic we get is\r\n```\r\nerror[E0080]: evaluation of constant expression failed\r\n --> src/main.rs:8:22\r\n  |\r\n8 |     println!(\"{:?}\", C);\r\n  |                      ^ referenced constant has errors\r\n\r\nerror: aborting due to previous error\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaking this an allowable lint is not very helpful when later follow-on errors are hard errors.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/65597/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/65597/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}